examples.en: Susan worked in the studios voluntarily, to gain experience.
She wasn't fired  she left voluntarily.
He was charged with voluntary manslaughter.
They voluntarily abnegated their temporal advantages.
When men act voluntarily, then they do what appears most agreeable to them.
Participation in the program is completely voluntary.
He was touched by the kindliness of his neighbors, who voluntarily took care of his dog while he was in the hospital.
